Package com.appglu.android.analytics

Contains the Analytics API implementation for Android.
This includes a service, a SQLite repository and the AnalyticsDispatcher abstraction and implementation.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
AnalyticsDispatcher Defines an strategy to where the AnalyticsSession are going to be sent.
ApiAnalyticsDispatcher is a implementation that will send the events to the AppGlu server.
AnalyticsRepository  
AnalyticsSessionCallback This callback allow you receive the AnalyticsSession objects before they saved or sent to the server.
This will allow you to change them before they are sent to the REST API.
 

Class Summary
AnalyticsApi AnalyticsApi is used to log events to AppGlu allowing it to collect mobile app usage statistics.
AnalyticsDatabaseHelper  
AnalyticsService  
ApiAnalyticsDispatcher ApiAnalyticsDispatcher is a implementation that will send the events to the AppGlu server.
LogAnalyticsDispatcher LogAnalyticsDispatcher is a implementation that will only log the events to the console.
SQLiteAnalyticsRepository  
 

Exception Summary
AnalyticsRepositoryException
